result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jabari Davaion Griffin in court, in custody.  Attorney Corey Flynn appears as a friend of the Court.  Attorney Dax Odom in court for State of Wisconsin. Case in court for pre-trial conference. Attorney Flynn informs the Court he has not yet been appointed on this case but expects to be soon. State informs the Court that along with the defendant's other pending matters in this court, a new global resolution could be negotiated to include this new case. Defense in agreement and requests a status date. Case adjourned. Case remains calendared in Br 15.
Status conference scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Court ordered no contact with KRS.
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5. 
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Jabari Davaion Griffin appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Katherine Elizabeth Holloway appeared by video for Jabari Davaion Griffin.  Prosecuting attorney Sara Beth Hill appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge J.D. Watts, Branch 15.   Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty. DEFENDANT DOES NOT QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDANT REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned to Branch 15 for pretrial conference.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 30, 2022 at 09:30 am.
